Dominion Bridge cuts McConnell stake . Dominion Bridge Corp of Canada said on Wednesday it had cut its stake in Australian construction group McConnell Dowell Corp Ltd to 63 . 03 percent from 77 . 42 percent . Dominion , formerly Cedar Group Inc , said earlier this month that it planned to cut its McConnell stake through the issue of six million shares to institutions . The Canadian construction group acquired control of McConnell through a A $ 1 . 60 per share takeover offer last year . At 11 . 40 a . m . ( 0040 GMT ) , McConnell shares were steady at A $ 2 . 25 in light volume . - - Sydney newsroom 61 - 2 9373 - 1800 
